.TH "hl_pin_host_memory" 9 "hl_pin_host_memory" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hl_pin_host_memory \- pins a chunk of host memory.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hl_pin_host_memory
.BI "(struct hl_device *hdev "  ","
.BI "u64 addr "  ","
.BI "u64 size "  ","
.BI "struct hl_userptr *userptr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hdev" 12
pointer to the habanalabs device structure.
.IP "addr" 12
the host virtual address of the memory area.
.IP "size" 12
the size of the memory area.
.IP "userptr" 12
pointer to hl_userptr structure.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function does the following:
- Pins the physical pages.
- Create an SG list from those pages.
